      • MIDINote

        public MIDINote()
        All default values.

      • MIDINote

        public MIDINote(int pitch)
        Initialize a new MIDINote with the specified pitch MIDI number. It will use the PitchFactory to retrieve a Pitch.

        Other instance variables are instantiated as follows:

        • startbeat = 1
        • duration = 1
        • channel = 0
        • bank = 0
        • program = 0
        • velocity = 64
        • pitchbend = 0
        • voice = 0 
         MIDINote n1 = new MIDINote(Pitch.C5);
        Parameters:
        pitch - The pitch midi number where 60 = middle C. (C5 in our numbering not C4)

      • MIDINote

        public MIDINote(int pitch,
        double startbeat,
        double duration,
        int channel,
        int velocity,
        int program,
        int bend,
        int bank,
        int voice)
        This is the constructor that is called by the other constructors which are just conveniences.
        MIDINote n1 = new MIDINote(Pitch.C5, 1d, 1d, 1, 64, 1, 0, 0, 0);
        Parameters:
        pitch - a MIDI number
        startbeat - the start beat
        duration - the duration
        channel - the MIDI channel
        velocity - the MIDI velocity
        program - the instrument program
        bend - pitch bend
        bank - the sound bank
        voice - the voice
        See Also:
        MIDINoteBuilder

      • MIDINote

        public MIDINote(Pitch pitch)
        Initialize a new MIDINote with the specified pitch.

        Other instance variables are instantiated as follows:

        • startbeat = 1
        • duration = 1
        • channel = 1
        • bank = 0
        • program = 1
        • velocity = 64
        • pitchbend = 0
        • voice = 1 
         MIDINote n1 = new MIDINote(PitchFactory.getPitch(Pitch.C5));
        Parameters:
        pitch - The pitch instance. Use a PitchFactory to retrieve one.
